8 years ago, I hit the slopes for the first time - a total novice, complete with vintage ski onesie⛷️❄️🧤It was super cold and I have to confess, I was far from a natural…but with a great group of pals, yummy French food (and a week at ski school), I was hooked! It was the first of many epic ski trips, and was even part of the inspiration for the LEGO Friends ski sets. And yes, I still rock the onesie whenever I get the chance 🙌 So be brave, and go learn something new this year…it might just become your fave thing ♥️
.

Did you know the name “LEGO” comes from the Danish words “leg godt,” meaning “play well?” For @brickmasteramy (Amy Corbett), who leads a team of designers creating some of the most desirable toys in the world, the idea of playing well is tantamount to working well. “We put kids at the center of our design process,” she says. “Our goal is to provide the best play experience possible.”

Glasgow, I ♥️ u!!! Fab day visiting the new Banksy exhibition at GoMA. If you don’t know him, he’s a fantastic street artist from UK. Love love loved it!!! The Duke of Wellington,  outside the gallery, has had a traffic cone on his head for as long as I can remember. No matter how hard the council tried to remove it -  someone always put it back. Now a true icon of Glasgow and a fave of Banksy himself 🙌

#streetart #banksy #glasgow #art #goma #inspiration #scotland

This week, I celebrated 10 years at the LEGO group 😱🍾🤩✨
Woweeeee, what a wild, awesome, magical & truly life-changing time it has been!!!! My wonderful colleagues spoiled me with lots of fabulous gifts, speeches and awesome memories 🎁 💕 🫶
I feel truly lucky to have my dream job doing what I love with the most talented bunch!!! So follow your dreams, and you never know where you might end up… Here’s to the next 10 years being just as fab!!! 🙌🙌🙌
#photodump 
📸2-4 From the fresh faced designer straight out of uni with her first box (of many), to being immortalised as a mini doll - LEGO Friends will always be my first love. 
📸5-6 Creating LEGO DOTS with the team has definitely been one of my career highlights. And we launched with a bang at the House of DOTS by @camillewalala 
📸 7 LEGO Masters has been the biggest adventure - bringing my passion for LEGO & design expertise to the screen with the best bunch. And seeing the awesome creativity of LEGO fans across!!!
📸8-9 To the many many awesome colleagues I now call friends, who make every day a blast 🤗 
📸10 And to life at LEGO HQ & in Denmark, where I now call home 🇩🇰
📸1 minidoll Amy portrait by the super talented @cheersfortheinvite

No matter the weather, Scotland will always have my heart ❤️ #AD 
Happy St Andrew’s day! 🏴󠁧󠁢󠁳󠁣󠁴󠁿 
I’ve been living and working in Denmark for 10 years now, but I love going back to Scotland whenever I get the chance. The gorgeous countryside, the warm and friendly people and their wild sense of humour! I love it all!!! Thanks everyone for sharing your fave bits of Scotland and contributing to this awesome artwork by @chelseafrew to celebrate all of our connections to Scotland this St Andrew's Day, wherever we are in the world!

Want to feel more connected to Scotland from afar? Check out https://www.scotland.org/about-scotland/international-relationships for more 

@ScotlandIsNow #StAndrewsDay23 #ScottishConnections
